Lady Shar does not see mercy as a virtue, even to simple creatures...

EditorData.NodeContext: Wrestling with her beliefs a little, though she's struggling to articulate it fully. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: The Shadowfell, her domain, has power here. Whatever the Dark Lady needs of me, I'll wager the answer lies wherever her power is strongest. I need to find that place, and see what awaits me.
A night orchid - remember I told you they were my favourite? I'm lucky to have found one - perhaps it's a good omen for us.

EditorData.NodeContext: pleased

Text.Value: Thank you, but I want you to refrain from foolish heroics - when the time comes, we will be entering a nest of vipers. I couldn't bear to lose you. Not after everything.
There will be more for me to do, no doubt. The holy work will not be done until the Nightsinger's eternal darkness is restored.
Worse than failed her - I defied her. Just because of what that aasimar said.
And this means I must have her blessing. Lady Shar is protecting me where others are left to face her wrath.
I... I don't want to, but Lady Shar demands it. Everything is surrendered to her, ultimately. But she claims some things earlier than others, it seems.

EditorData.NodeContext: Conflicted. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: You're not leaving, are you?
Even your Mother Superior couldn't prevent you from realising your dream.
Thank you, for saving a daughter of Selûne.
That's not the first time you've made such a leap.
He's trouble - worse, he's a traitor. Whatever loyalty he had towards Lady Shar is long gone. It would please her greatly to see him meet his long-overdue end, I'll wager.

EditorData.NodeContext: Some contempt towards the person she's discussing - a onetime paladin of shar who changed allegiances. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: Good. I did this for Lady Shar, for myself... but I had hoped you'd like it as well.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little relieved

Text.Value: I thought I knew who I was... but I was wrong. I do not belong to Shar, and I do not want to be adorned like one of her puppets any longer.
Take a moment, if you need it. I didn't know this would happen - truly.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sincere. Doesn't regret what she did, but regrets that it upset her love interest/respected player

Text.Value: Yet it was just a reminder of who I truly serve. I am still loyal to Lady Shar, and she will still offer me protection from some of her power.

EditorData.NodeContext: Reasoning with herself. Arc: SH is loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: This is your fault.
Have you ever heard of the Dark Justiciars? They were Lady Shar's most elite warriors. I can't explain why, but something about this reminds me of them.
These doubts... where do you think they stem from?
Silently pray for those lost. Urge the Moonmaiden to guide their spirits to her light.
You'll need to make some room for me first - seems like you have ample company already.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little subdued, preoccupied . Arc: SH has recently defied Shar by not killing Nightsong. Now she's processing the fact that she's been banished by her goddess, and will remain in this slump until she speaks to Nightsong again to learn more about herself.

Text.Value: I'm glad... though I don't think I'm quite done with the past yet. Not until I've been to Baldur's Gate.
Join me.
You're too quick to find excuses for Shar. She turned on you.
With good reason. It is no coincidence that a daughter of the Moonmaiden spoke to you of wolves.
I don't have anything to give you in return, I'm afraid.
We need to get to Baldur's Gate, first of all.
I'll admit it, staying true to Lady Shar has proved difficult at times. I've found that my mind is prone to wandering.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wrestling with her beliefs a little, though she's struggling to articulate it fully. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: Well, I'm glad someone does. Perhaps I'll get used to it. I have a lot to get used to, right now.
I suppose that cleric, Isobel, must seem impressive to you - wielding Selûnite magic, resisting Lady Shar's darkness...
That cleric, Isobel - she seems almost impressive, in a perverse sort of way. I didn't think anyone could resist Lady Shar's power like she does.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grudging respect for Isobel, a selunite she met.  Arc: SH is loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: The shadow curse - does it affect you now?
This hairstyle is closer to Lady Shar's own image. I did it to honour her... what do you think?

EditorData.NodeContext: Brave face/touch of nerves. She's revealing a new hairstyle to the player, in the image of shar (arc: Shar path, SH has sacrificed Nightsong)

Text.Value: Perhaps we'll still be able to find a way. Some interpretation of her will that let's us stay together. But I can't guarantee anything, and I suspect that she'll demand more and more of me, as time passes.

EditorData.NodeContext: Conflicted. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: I don't fully know... just a nagging feeling. Almost like I'm conflicted about something, but I don't quite know what.

EditorData.NodeContext: Vaguely troubled/struggling to articulate something.

Text.Value: Normally, I'd tell you you're just reading too much into things. But, well...

EditorData.NodeContext: Wrestling with her beliefs a little, though she's struggling to articulate it fully. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: I do. I've wanted this for a long time.
Thinking about my wound... it can't just be random, how it torments me. Surely there's a pattern, a purpose...

EditorData.NodeContext: Wrestling with her beliefs a little, though she's struggling to articulate it fully. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: Give it time. It may grow on you.
You're resourceful - you'll find a way. Don't give me that look. It's a good thing that I'm resistant to the shadows - this way I can help you.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Sceptical reaction from the player after SH's first line. Back to SH right after, looking defensive.
EditorData.NodeContext: A little defensive on the second sentence (reacting to player's displeased look)

Text.Value: Shar's power will soon wane in these lands...
Everyone has doubts. You're not special.
Don't thank me. I didn't do it for her. I'm not even sure I did it for me.
Don't get carried away - this could be something else.
Perhaps you should try to appease Shar. She may forgive you.
We'll just have to keep going, and see what lies ahead.
Still, though... I wonder if there's more to it. Surely they could have held out at the inn for at least a while... unless they, too, felt Nightsong's passing.

EditorData.NodeContext: Conjecture. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: I... I thought I was done for. I thought perhaps I might have been dead.

EditorData.NodeContext: Shaken. Speaking shortly after she's been ostracised by Shar for defying her.

Text.Value: Honest of you. And you're right - this is about me, and how I can best serve Lady Shar.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grudging respect. Player admitted they don't like her new hair.

Text.Value: I don't know. You seem a little less focused on your mission, perhaps.
Thank you. I needed that.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quietly emptional/appreciative post-hug. Speaking shortly after she's been ostracised by Shar for defying her.

Text.Value: Not as glad as I am.

EditorData.NodeContext: Proud. Has proven herself to her goddess. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: I've always felt like I owed Lady Shar my life... but what came before? Why was I in those woods?

EditorData.NodeContext: Wrestling with her beliefs a little, though she's struggling to articulate it fully. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: That blessing you accepted - Lady Shar won't like it, but I have to hope she'll understand it was a necessary evil.

EditorData.NodeContext: Some concern/trying to square a circle. Arc: SH is loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: Be honest... what do you think of the new look?

EditorData.NodeContext: A little nervous. Revealing a new hairstyle

Text.Value: And please - the less said about her blessing, the better. That was for your benefit, and to keep the peace.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wince of embarassment at the thought.  Arc: SH is loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: I'm sure you'll come up with something, in time.
Nightsong will be able to give you answers, when the time comes.
Indeed. And already I have seen to some of her holy work - the apostate Ketheric Thorm is dead. He stole Lady Shar's powers to extend his profane life. No more.
Not for me - but who cares?
Then I can only hope Lady Shar will prove lenient if I try to keep a little piece of my heart from her...

EditorData.NodeContext: Pleased but also nervous. At risk of upsetting her goddess with sacrilegious romance. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: We'll see. Give me a while to put my imagination to work.

EditorData.NodeContext: playful/flirty

Text.Value: Nightsong... she mentioned your fear of wolves, just like you shared with me. That's no coincidence.
I love it.
I intend to. I've wasted enough time serving others.
That's what concerns me... I don't know. Perhaps there's something about me, waiting to be discovered. Something I won't like.
Perhaps this is it for us then. I'll still cherish our time together.
He betrayed Lady Shar. There can be no forgiveness for that.

EditorData.NodeContext: Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: My parents are alive, and I have to save them. I think a part of me always knew that - a part that Shar denied to me.

EditorData.NodeContext: A lot to process, emotionally. Arc: Shadowheart has rejected Shar

Text.Value: I... I think so, yes. Perhaps I shouldn't put it to the test, but compared to everyone else, I feel fine. Better than fine.

EditorData.NodeContext: Can't believe it

Text.Value: Yes, I'm counting on it - I have little else to turn to.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little subdued, preoccupied . Arc: SH has recently defied Shar by not killing Nightsong. Now she's processing the fact that she's been banished by her goddess, and will remain in this slump until she speaks to Nightsong again to learn more about herself.

Text.Value: If it helps you put the past behind you, I'm all for it.
This must mean she is protecting me - she favours me... and you don't even know what I mean, do you? Time to come clean I suppose.

Synopsis: Default dialogue - the conversation you can have with Shadowheart at any time when she's a member of your party. You can ask her about herself, or events that you've experienced together during your adventures. Her responses to you may differ slightly depending on her current attitude towards you.
